column7: SPAIN BARCELONA KNOX, IN COOPERATION WITH THE UNIVERSITY OF BARCELONA, OFFERS ACADEMIC STUDY IN LANGUAGE, THE HUMANITIES AND THE SOCIAL SCIENCES. STUDENTS PURSUE A COMBINATION OF COURSES, ALL TAUGHT IN SPANISH BY PROFESSORS FROM THE UNIVERSITY OF BARCELONA. SOME OF THE COURSES ARE FITTED TO THE PARTICULAR NEEDS OF PROGRAM STUDENTS, OTHER COURSES ARE FROM THE REGULAR UNIVERSITY CURRICULUM OFFERED TO SPANISH STUDENTS. ALL STUDENTS LIVE IN THE HOMES OF SPANISH FAMILIES IN BARCELONA. THE PROGRAM HAS A TWO-WEEK TRIP THROUGHOUT SOUTHERN SPAIN DURING WINTER BREAK AS WELL AS OTHER SHORTER EDUCATIONAL FIELD TRIPS.

column7: The Board of Directors, which includes John De Margheriti, President and Treasurer, and Vicki De Margheriti, Vice President and Secretary for AIE - LA reside in Australia and often travel outside of Australia. All board meetings during this fiscal year were conducted in Australia and abroad. Board resolutions were communicated to the AIE - LA campus via E-mail attachments. Board inquiries and communication with the AIE - LA school were conducted via electronic means, such as Skype and Google Hangout. Also, at least one member of the board performs a physical visit to the AIE - LA location on an annual basis to ensure that Board resolutions are implemented.

The AIE, Ltd. provides AIE - LA with IT, Marketing, Curricular, Bundled Software Licensing, and Accounting support. In accordance with a decision made by the Board of Directors, AIE - LA now reimburses The AIE, Ltd. for its share of these expenses on an annual and semi-annual basis. Staff cost $16,649; Software cost $24,605.
AIE - LA pays The AIE, Ltd. an IP consideration for the use of curriculum content per the Copyright License Agreement - Amended January 1, 2019.

column7: The Board of Directors, which includes John De Margheriti, President and Treasurer, and Vicki De Margheriti, Vice President and Secretary for AIE - WA reside in Australia and often travel outside of Australia. All board meetings during this fiscal year were conducted in Australia. Board resolutions were communicated to the AIE - WA campus via E-mail attachments. Board inquiries and communication with the AIE - WA school were conducted via electronic means, such as Teams and Email. Also, at least one member of the board performs a physical visit to the AIE - WA location on an annual basis to ensure that Board resolutions are implemented.

The AIE, Ltd. provides AIE - WA with IT, Marketing, Curricular, Bundled Software Licensing, and Accounting support. In accordance with a decision made by the Board of Directors, AIE - WA now reimburses The AIE, Ltd. for its share of these expenses on an annual and semi-annual basis. Staff cost $30,326; Travel cost $36,531; Software cost $30,895.
AIE - WA pays The AIE, Ltd. an IP consideration for the use of curriculum content per the Copyright License Agreement - Amended January 1, 2019.
